        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer35539769" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13245698810866342671">I found this book good at the start, but slightly dry and disappointing. The story is compelling enough be then it meanders off into nowhere, really, and ends with the investigation stalling. So, basically they went through all of that for nothing. Sometimes, real life is stranger than fiction - but in this case, it&apos;s probably more boring than fiction would be. At the end of a fictional novel, the killer would have been unmasked and good will have triumphed over evil. In this version, the evil w</span>
  <span id="freeText13245698810866342671" style="display:none">I found this book good at the start, but slightly dry and disappointing. The story is compelling enough be then it meanders off into nowhere, really, and ends with the investigation stalling. So, basically they went through all of that for nothing. Sometimes, real life is stranger than fiction - but in this case, it's probably more boring than fiction would be. At the end of a fictional novel, the killer would have been unmasked and good will have triumphed over evil. In this version, the evil was split between some weird Florentine families and a lazy police deparment...all in their quest for notoriety and power - and I have to say I need to include the two authors in this.<br />Egotistically speaking, they ended up making this story more about themselves than the killer - it's no wonder no one turned up any new evidence.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13245698810866342671" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
